o século XVI -- tPremières images françaises du Brésil -- tLarissa e o sonho das passagens: história como deslocamento -- tPerspectivas brasileiras -- tO Brasil como “país do futuro” nas imaginações livrescas de Policarpo Quaresma -- tA “Nota preliminar” d’Os sertões -- tUm tempo antropófago para um espaço multicultural. Notas sobre antropofagia e multiculturalismo -- tAinda existem “Os dois Brasis”? Sobre as estruturas sociais e as imagens da estrutura social no Brasil -- tPoesía brasileña -- tPráticas de representação luso-brasileiras do século XVII -- tÍndice onomástico -- tBiobibliografia0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aGegenstand des vorliegenden Bandes ist die Untersuchung der mannigfaltigen Beziehungen Brasiliens zu den hispanoamerikanischen Nachbar-Ländern. Der lateinamerikanische Kontext, in den Brasilien eingebettet ist, wird durch ein verschiedenartiges Netz bi- und multilateraler Beziehungen bestimmt, welches bisher in der Forschung wenig Beachtung gefunden hat. Der Band versteht sich als Beitrag zur Reflexion der interkulturellen Dynamik dieser Beziehungen. Die Interdisziplinarität der Beiträge ist weitgespannt. Sie umfaßt neben Ansätzen aus dem Bereich der Literatur- und Filmwissenschaft, der Philosophie, den Sozial- und Politikwissenschaften auch solche aus dem Bereich der Anthropologie, der Geschichte und der Theologie.  aThis volume is devoted to an examination of the vast range of relations existing between Brazil and its Hispano-American neighbours. The Latin American context in which Brazil is embedded is determined by a multifarious network of bi- and multi-lateral relations that has been given little attention by scholars so far. The volume sets out to make a contribution to a closer engagement with the intercultural dynamics informing those relations. The cross-disciplinary aspect is very marked. Alongside articles from representatives of literary and film studies, philosophy, and the social and political sciences, there are also studies illuminating theological, historical, and anthropological aspects. Discutir as múltiplas relações do Brasil com os países hispano-americanos é o objetivo deste volume. O Brasil situa-se em um contexto latino-americano que é constituído por uma rede de intercâmbios diversificada, que curiosamente tende a passar desapercebida. O presente volume pretende contribuir para a reflexão desta dinâmica intercultural a partir de uma proposta interdisciplinar. As Américas do Sul são discutidas, assim, através de uma variedade de enfoques que envolvem as seguintes áreas: crítica literária e cinematográfica, filosofia, ciências sociais e políticas, antropologia, história e teologia.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Portuguese.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aBrasilien. 4aHispanoamerika. 4aKulturbeziehungen. 4aKulturkontakt. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aAvellar, José Carlos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarbieri, Ivo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerg, Walter Bruno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerg, Walter Bruno, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBoff, Leonardo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBriesemeister, Dietrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFreire, José Ribamar Bessa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiucci, Guillermo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHansen, João Adolfo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHardman, Francisco Foot, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJurt, Joseph, econtrib